<s> Paul, You could add a class to those sections ( span class="ww" the get out bit /span or p class="ww" a wholoe paragraph /p in HTML) along with a style that makes those things red, or loud, or whatever (according to the media used).  </s>
<s> Alternatively you could emphasise them ( p some em get out stuff /em /p ) since the em element has a default rendering in most systems.  </s>
<s> If you wanted to you could put a class attribute on the em element ( em class="ww" ).  </s>
<s> Either way, you could provide a style for the element that made it red, or in a squeaky voice, or whatever.  </s>
<s> This question should be answered in the Techniques for Web Content Accessibility Guidelines - http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG10-TECHS - since it is about how to meet checkpoint 2.2 of the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines.  </s>
